This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image restoration and object detection, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of various loss functions and advanced modules, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of perception-driven loss, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning and falls under cs.LG. The paper also discusses the use of domain-adaptive object detectors, which is a technique commonly used in graphics and visualization, hence cs.GR is also a likely category. Finally, the paper deals with image datasets and benchmarks, which is a topic commonly discussed in multimedia and multimodal processing, hence cs.MM is also a likely category.
